Text.Value: Dragon-spawn, you are truly worthy of containing the Lord of Murder's immortal essence.
There is no shame greater than failing in his service. But even so, each death is a gift.
Spawn, you speak to another of your fallen family. It is heartening to see a child once again brimming with promise.
You are an inspiration to our kind.
We hunted down his insipid fledglings in droves, until we were all that was left. All but Sarevok's own murderer, who murdered me in turn.
I thought I was the only dragonborn Bhaalspawn...
Bring deaths for Bhaal, hallowed child, or die in his name.
I've never heard of a dragonborn Bhaalspawn.
Show me your wares.
Hail, Unholy Assassin, sublime malfeasor.
Tell me of the Five.
Yes. Father Bhaal mated with a true dragon. Pray one day you have the honour of doing the same.
All us wretched spectres, Bhaal's failures, are watching your rise with great anticipation.
Honoured Spawn, have you come to peruse the instruments once more?
Leave.
I offer you instruments which will aid in enacting your foul whims.
I am no half-blooded drake. Alive, I was a dragon of pure cerulean chrome. But oft the need arose to disguise myself thus.
You have killed well, Unholy Assassin. I am here to further your slaughter.
The Five, my order of Father's spawn, were among the first to carve the philosophy that Sarevok's death began.
The perfect child, from the strongest stock. He made you well.
I found an effigy of your death.
The weakness was my disgrace, but it was an honour to give myself to Bhaal's embrace.
Go forth, Unholy Assassin, desecrate in your stride.
We led our worship by killing the weakest of our own line, writing kin-slaying into the canon.
In life, I was Abazigal, kin-killer of the Five. In death, I serve our Father still - until the world grows silent.

Synopsis: After completing the Murder Tribunal trial and completing the Baptism of Blood, the Echo of Abazigal will appear in the courtroom to provide you with Bhaalist/assassiny wares. Abazigal was one of the Five Bhaalspawn from BG2: Throne of Bhaal.
